don]]\n| \n|-\n| \u2013\n|IOE Lond<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|\n|[[Institute of Education]], London\n|Now part of [[University College London|UCL]]\n|-\n|Cantuar{{refn|{{cite web|url=http://www.stmarys.ac.uk/arts-and-humanities/staff/lance-pettitt.htm#page=teaching|publisher=[[St Mary's University, Twickenham]]|title=Profile: Prof Lance Pettitt BA (Cantaur)[sic] MA PhD (NUI Dublin)|accessdate=20 December 2015}} \u2013 according to his CV, Prof. Pettitt earned his BA at Kent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stmarys.ac.uk/arts-and-humanities/staff/research/Lance-Pettitt.pdf|title=Lance Pettitt|accessdate=20 December 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222112510/http://www.stmarys.ac.uk/arts-and-humanities/staff/research/Lance-Pettitt.pdf|archivedate=22 December 2015}}</ref>}}\n| \u2013 (Kent)\n|''Cantuariensis'' (=&nbsp;Canterbury) or ''Cantiensis''\n|[[University of Kent]]\n|Use of Cantuar for Kent is rare and risks confusion with both [[Lambeth degrees]] and the [[University of Canterbury]], NZ. The Latin name for Kent is Cantium (hence ''Cantiensis'') which would give ''Cant'' (also used by the University of Canterbury, NZ); the University of Kent was originally the University of Kent at Canterbury.\n|-\n| \u2013\n|KCL<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|''Collegium Regium apud Londinenses''<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=g6xAAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA526|title=Address from King's College London|page=526|work=Record of the Celebration of the Quatercentenary of the University of Aberdeen|publisher=University of Aberdeen|date=1907}}</ref>\n|[[King's College London]]\n|For pre-2008 award, use [[University of London]]'s post nominal abbreviation.<ref name=\"kcl.ac.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kcl.ac.uk/campuslife/services/examinations/certificates/certificates.aspx|title=King's College London \u2013 Certificate production|publisher=King's College London}}</ref> Certain period from 2008 allowed respective graduates to choose from the two awarding bodies.<ref name=\"kcl.ac.uk\"/>\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|Lanc<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|''Lancastriensis''\n|[[University of Lancaster]]\n|\n|-\n| \u2013\n| ULaw\n|''Collegium iurisprudentiae''\n|[[University of Law]]\n| Previously known as The College of Law\n|-\n| \u2013\n|Leeds Met<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|\n|[[Leeds Beckett University]]\n|Used to be referred to as Leeds Metropolitan\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|Leic<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|''Leicestriensis''\n|[[University of Leicester]]\n|\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|Linc<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|''Lincolniensis''\n|[[University of Lincoln]]\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-style:solid solid none solid;\"|Liv,<ref name=OxCalendar/>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Liverpolis''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[University of Liverpool]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|&nbsp;\n|-\n| style=\"border-style:none solid solid solid;\"|&nbsp;\n|Lpool<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gdc-uk.org/pages/GDCSearchResults.aspx?RegNumber=42840&Surname=crawford&Forenames=alex&isSoundexFN=0&isSoundexSN=0&Town=&Postcode=&isDentist=1&isDCP=0&isSpecialist=0&Speciality=&DCPTitle=&IER=0&isAllRegisters=0&sbk=1|title=GDC Search Results|publisher=[[General Dental Council]]|accessdate=21 December 2015|quote=\"Qualifications: DDPH RCS Eng 1972 MSc Lond 1974 PhD Lpool 1995 BDS Lpool 1968\"|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222110839/http://www.gdc-uk.org/pages/GDCSearchResults.aspx?RegNumber=42840&Surname=crawford&Forenames=alex&isSoundexFN=0&isSoundexSN=0&Town=&Postcode=&isDentist=1&isDCP=0&isSpecialist=0&Speciality=&DCPTitle=&IER=0&isAllRegisters=0&sbk=1|archivedate=22 December 2015}}</ref> or L'pool<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/obits_alpha/nairn_richard.pdf|publisher=[[The Royal Society]]|title=Richard Nairn|accessdate=21 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222122424/https://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/obits_alpha/nairn_richard.pdf|archive-date=22 December 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| \u2013\n|Liv H